Great question! When you're chatting with me, your temporary chat history is saved for 30 days. During that time, you can access it as long as you're logged into the same account and using a platform that supports chat history.

Here’s how to access it, depending on where you're using ChatGPT:

🧠 If you're on the ChatGPT web app (chat.openai.com):

  1. On the left sidebar, you'll see a list of your past chats.

  2. Chats are usually labeled with a summary or just "New Chat" until renamed.

  3. You can click any one of those to open it up — even if it’s a few weeks old (as long as it’s within 30 days).

  4. After 30 days, temporary chats are automatically deleted unless you’ve saved or exported them manually.

📱 If you’re using the ChatGPT mobile app:

  1. Tap the hamburger menu (☰) in the top-left corner.

  2. Your recent chats will show up there.

  3. Tap to re-enter a previous conversation.

⚠️ If you don’t see old chats:

  • You might be in private browsing mode.

  • You may not be logged into the correct account.

  • Or your history setting might be turned off.

i have just 5 followers on tiktok but my views are higher like 145 views but then when you check my facebook with 3.5k followers i dont get up to 100 view what is wrong
ChatGPT said:

Ahhh, this is such a relatable situation — and you're definitely not alone in wondering what’s going on. Social media can be weird like that. Let’s break down what’s likely happening here:

🧨 Why TikTok Is Getting You More Views (with just 5 followers):

TikTok is discovery-first. That means:

  • The "For You Page" (FYP) shows your video to strangers first, not just your followers.

  • Their algorithm is super aggressive about testing your content with random users to see how it performs.

  • Even new accounts with 0 followers can get hundreds or thousands of views if the content hits.

So, 5 followers doesn’t really matter — TikTok's reach is based more on how your video performs in those first few seconds (watch time, engagement, completion rate).

😒 Why Facebook Isn’t Showing Your Content to Your 3.5k Followers:

Facebook is follower-first, but with low organic reach. Here's what's likely happening:

  • Facebook pages and even profiles get throttled unless you’re paying for promotion or have super engaged followers.

  • Only a tiny percentage (sometimes less than 5%) of your followers see your posts in their feed unless:

    • They regularly engage with your content.

    • Or it gets early likes/comments/shares.

Also, Facebook is a bit more saturated and slow compared to TikTok’s rapid-fire attention system.

🔧 What You Can Do About It:

On TikTok:

  • Keep posting consistently. You're actually doing well if you’re getting 145 views with 5 followers — TikTok is pushing your content!

  • Use relevant trending sounds, hashtags, and hook viewers in the first 2 seconds.

On Facebook:

  • Try video content instead of just photo/text posts.

  • Ask your core followers to like/comment/share early (even a few people doing this boosts reach).

  • Consider cross-posting your TikToks to Facebook Reels.

  • Or invite your Facebook followers to follow you on TikTok (bring the crowd where the energy is!).
